 Business Briefs
																								 London, Oct. 16: Oil thundered towards $88 a barrel on Tuesday, hitting a new record. Oil is closing in on the inflation-adjusted high of $90.46 seen in 1980. Prices this year have averaged $67. At 7:08 a.m., the US crude was up $1.33 at $87.46, off a high of $87.97. London Brent was up $1.22 at $83.97. Theres a lot of risk there and that is being reflected in the price, said fund manager David Dugdale of MFC Global Investment Management.																								 Calcutta, Oct. 16: Dunlop India has absorbed 1,202 workers as permanent employees in its Sahaganj unit and has started production. In its agreement with trade unions, the company has committed itself to induct 1,179 old employees as permanent staff.																								 Calcutta, Oct. 16: Merrill Lynch has picked up a 5 per cent stake in Ranbaxy-promoted Religare Enterprises Ltd for Rs 62 crore. The stake buy came on the eve of Religare hitting the capital markets with an initial public offering of 1.14 crore equities to raise between Rs 150 crore and Rs 160 crore. 																								 Mumbai, Oct. 16: The Bank of America today announced an infusion of $83 million (Rs 330 crore) into its India operations. The Tier I capital of the banks India branches has increased to $466 million.																								 Mumbai Oct. 16: The Industrial Development Bank of India (IDBI) today posted a net profit of Rs 155.50 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 139.40 crore a year ago.
